ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: It's an amazingly fulfilling and challenging course. If you take it and are willing to put the hours in (at least 10 a week, sometimes much more), you'll do well and will get a lot out of it. This is the sort of course you build your class schedule around, though, not the sort of thing you add as an afterthought.
Interesting, hands-on and up-to-date introduction to OS design, this was a great course.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: OS development touches upon many fundamental aspects of applied CS, including data structures, parallel processing, synchronization mechanisms, memory allocation, and much more. I learned an incredible amount from this class.
It contributed significantly. I feel comfortable diving into complex systems projects now.
